{"lemma":"مُقَدَّس","slug":"مُقَدَّس","root":"ق.د.س","root_slug":"ق-د-س","root_link":"/words/roots/ق-د-س","pos":"ADJ","pos_camel":"adj","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"مُقَدَّس","root":"قدس","pos":"N","occurrence_count":2},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":2,"pos_tags":["adj","noun"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":4},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n35312","n35313"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D9%85%D9%8F%D9%82%D9%8E%D8%AF%D9%8E%D9%91%D8%B3"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"a holy place; a sanctuary"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"sacred, holy"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"sanctified"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"consecrated"}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"ِApparently an irregular noun of place from قَدُسَ (qadusa, “to be holy”), occurring chiefly in an Arabic name for the Temple in Jerusalem, بَيْت المَقْدِس (bayt al-maqdis, “The House of the Holy Place”), with the regular form being مَقْدَس (maqdas). Compare مَطْلَع (maṭlaʕ, “rising place”) and its irregular variant, مَطْلِع (maṭliʕ). Compare also the irregular مَنْكِب (mankib, “shoulder-joint”), a derivation that Sībawayh, however, suspected to be a name for this body part rather than a noun of place.\nCompare with Aramaic מַקְדְּשָׁא (maqdəšā), Hebrew מִקְדָּשׁ (miqdāsh), Punic 𐤌𐤉𐤒𐤃𐤔 (myqdš).\n\nDerived from the passive participle of قَدَّسَ (qaddasa, “to sanctify, to make holy, to consecrate”)."},"ipa":null,"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n35312","headword_ar":"مُقَدَّسٌ","root":"qds","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Hallowed,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"sanctified: consecrated: purified:"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"blessed."},{"kind":"text","text":"(M.) ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Almuqad~asu","text_ar":"المُقَدَّسُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", applied to God: see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alqud~uwsu","text_ar":"القُدُّوسُ"},{"kind":"text","text":". ―         -b3-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Albayotu Almuqad~asu","text_ar":"البَيْتُ المُقَدَّسُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bayotu Almuqad~asi","text_ar":"بَيْتُ المُقَدَّسِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, K,) and [more commonly]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bayotu","text_ar":"بَيْتُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Almaqodisi","text_ar":"المَقْدِسِ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (M, A, K,) which [i. e."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Almaqodis","text_ar":"المَقْدِس"},{"kind":"text","text":"] is either formed from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"muqad~asN","text_ar":"مُقَدَّسٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"by rejecting the augmentative letter, or is a subst. not formed from a verb, like as Sb says of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Almanokibu","text_ar":"المَنْكِبُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (M,) [signifying"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The hallowed,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"consecrated,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"purified,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"blessed, dwelling;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the dwelling of the hallowed,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.; are appellations of"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Jerusalem;"},{"kind":"text","text":"] also called ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alqudosu","text_ar":"القُدْسُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"[which is the name generally given to it in the present day] and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alqudusu","text_ar":"القُدُسُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (A, K;) because one is purified therein from sins, or because of the blessing that is therein. (TA.) ―         -b4-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlA^aroDu Almuqad~asapu","text_ar":"الاَرْضُ المُقَدَّسَةُ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"hallowed,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"consecrated,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"purified land;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Msb, K;) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the pure land;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Fr;) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the blessed land;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(IAar;) is an appellation of"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Damascus and Palestine and part of the Jordan:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Fr:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Syria:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M:) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aroDu Alqudusi","text_ar":"اَرْضُ القُدُسِ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aroDu Alqudosi","text_ar":"اَرْضُ القُدْسِ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"] signifies the same. (TA.)"}],"source_refs":["K","S","M","A","Fr"]},{"entry_id":"n35313","headword_ar":"مُقَدِّسٌ","root":"qds","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"A Christian monk [or any Christian or a Jew]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"who comes"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"goes"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"performs pilgrimage"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"has performed pilgrimage"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alqudos","text_ar":"القُدْس"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bayot","text_ar":"بَيْت"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Almaqodis","text_ar":"المَقْدِس"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Jerusalem"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (A:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a Christian monk:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"learned Jew"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"other, such as is called"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Habor","text_ar":"حَبْر"},{"kind":"text","text":". (M, TA.) Imra-el-Keys says, describing dogs and a [wild] bull,"},{"kind":"quote","text":"faA^adorakonahu yaA^oxu*ona biAls~aAqi waAln~asaA\n                      \n                     \n                        kamaA $aboraqa AlwilodaAnu vawoba Almuqad~isi"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"And they"},{"kind":"text","text":"(the dogs)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"overtook him,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(namely, the bull,) seizing the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"shank and the sciatic vein,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and tearing his skin,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"as the children"},{"kind":"text","text":"of the Christians"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"tear the garment of the monk that has come from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bayot Almaqodis","text_ar":"بَيْت المَقْدِس"},{"kind":"text","text":", [or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Jerusalem"},{"kind":"text","text":"] for the purpose of obtaining a blessing from it: thus the verse is found in the handwriting of Aboo-Sahl; but in all the copies of the S, we find"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"vawoba Almuqad~asiY","text_ar":"ثَوْبَ المُقَدَّسِى"},{"kind":"text","text":", with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Y","text_ar":"ى"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.)"}],"source_refs":["A","K"]}]}}